text: Nectandra matudai is a species of plant in the family Lauraceae. It is endemic to Chiapas and Oaxaca states, located in southwestern Mexico. ==References== matudai Category:Endemic flora of Mexico Category:Trees of Chiapas Category:Trees of Oaxaca Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot Category:Endangered flora of North America
